    "diagnosis": {
        "final_diagnosis": "pheochromocytoma with coexisting non-ACTH-dependent cortisol hypersecretion",
        "diagnostic_reasoning": "The patient presented with mild Cushing’s stigmata, hypertension, and diabetes mellitus. Hormonal work-up revealed elevated urinary catecholamines and dexamethasone non-suppressible hypercortisolism with low ACTH levels, suggesting non-ACTH-dependent cortisol hypersecretion. MRI findings and positive immunostaining for IL-6 in the pheochromocytoma suggested paracrine stimulation of the ipsilateral adrenal cortex by IL-6, leading to cortical hyperplasia and subclinical Cushing’s syndrome."
